Records of the Office of the President (John Brademas)

Contents

Series I. Administration, 1973-2001

Extent

9.60 Linear Feet in 23 manuscript boxes.

Scope and Contents

This series contains Brademas' appointment books from 1981 to 1991, documenting his daily events and meetings. Other files include material related to the Bobst Award; honorary degrees; selection process for departmental chairs and visiting professors; fundraising; and university program development. Information on NYU's overseas programs; the Urban Studies and Research Center; the Grey Art Gallery; and the Japanese Business Center are in this series. The "JB Project" files appear to be ideas fostered by Brademas, including a Chinese University Presidents' group visit to NYU and a potential Latin American Foreign Ministers Conference. Brademas' travel briefing books in this series were created for his trips taken between 1989 to 1990 to Greece, Cyprus, and France. These briefing books typically contain schedules, support material for meetings, and profiles on people he would meet during the trip. Similar travel briefing material can also be found in Series VII.

Series II. Alumni Affairs, 1980-1991

Extent

2.10 Linear Feet in 5 manuscript boxes.

Scope and Contents

This series includes material accumulated by the President's office on NYU's Alumni Council, Alumni Federation, and Alumni Relations. These files typically contain meeting minutes, correspondence, and awards material.

31142067124787box: 21, folder: 8 (Material Type: Mixed Materials)

Series III. Associations, 1973-1990

Extent

7.51 Linear Feet in 18 manuscript boxes.

Scope and Contents

This series contains files collected by Brademas on organizations he regularly interacted with or served in some capacity. The files typically contain organization reports, publications, correspondence, and meeting notes. Organizations with files containing a significant amount of material include the American Academy of Arts and Sciences; Academy for Educational Development; American Council on Education; Association of American Universities; Association of Colleges and Universities of New York; Commission on Independent Colleges and Universities; Federal Reserve Bank; Onassis Foundation; United Way; and the Rockefeller Foundation.

Series VII. Governance, 1952-1992

Extent

14.60 Linear Feet in 35 manuscript boxes.

Scope and Contents

Most of the files in this series are NYU Board of Trustees material dating from 1980 to 1990, including meeting minutes and agendas, President's Reports, committee information, individual member files, and Presidents' Congratulatory files. This series also contains files related to Brademas' trips to Japan, Asia, Poland, Spain, South America, and Yugoslavia on behalf of NYU, which would often involve Board of Trustees members. University Senate meeting files found in this series date from 1980 to 1991 and usually contain minutes, reports, correspondence, and agendas.

Conditions Governing Access

Access to this series is restricted until 2027.

Cost Allocation Reports, 1981-1982

31142067124860box: 240, folder: 6 (Material Type: Mixed Materials)

Series VIII. Governmental Relations, 1961-1990

Extent

8.76 Linear Feet in 21 manuscript boxes.

Scope and Contents

This series contains correspondence, reports, budgets, and publications accumulated by the President's office from federal and state government departments and agencies which impacted NYU during the 1980s and early 1990s. Material dates from 1965 to 1990 and contains information on specific federal departments including the Department of Labor; Department of Defense; and Department of the Interior, as well as agencies including U.S. Department of Housing and Urban Development (HUD); National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA); and the National Endowment for the Arts (NEA). Files in this series also contain information generated by the U.S. House of Representatives, the Senate, and New York State Senate and Assembly. Additionally, this series includes subject files containing reports and other publications on student loans, taxes, and drugs in schools.

Series IX. Art and Memorabilia, 1975-1991

Extent

3 Linear Feet in 1 flat box, 1 oversize box, and 1 flat-file folder.

Scope and Contents

This series contains an artwork gifted to Brademas and his wife by the artist Chaim Gross; a collage art piece with storage case; and an academic gown hood worn by Brademas during ceremonies.

Limited Edition Print of NYU Motto and Torch, Presented to President Brademas, 1981

Academic Hood for Graduation Robe, undated

31142063063492box: 293 (Material Type: Mixed Materials)

Series X. Public Relations, 1975-1991

Extent

22 Linear Feet in 47 manuscript boxes and 1 flat box.
33 videocassettes (vhs)

Scope and Contents

This series mainly contains public relations office material related to appearances and events Brademas attended or organized while serving as President of NYU. Files in this series contain requests for Brademas appearances and speeches; planning files for NYU events; and correspondence. A small collection of speeches in this series date from 1981 to 1984; however, a more comprehensive set can be found in Series XIII. Planning files for events hosted in Brademas' penthouse residence are in this series and typically include invitation lists, menus, and schedules. Clippings and press releases in this series feature Brademas and his connection to NYU. Photographic portraits of Brademas, as well as event photographs are in this series. Event photographs include parties at the Onassis Center in Greece, and Brademas' trips to Asia. A large number of video recordings in this series contain footage for a possible informational video for NYU's Villa La Pietra in Florence, Italy. These videos contain interviews with Sir Harold Acton, views of the building and grounds, and historical stock footage.

Series XI. Schools and Divisions, 1977-1991

Extent

20.43 Linear Feet in 49 manuscript boxes.

Scope and Contents

This series includes reports, speeches, correspondence, budgets, and annual reports collected by the Office of the President on individual NYU Schools and Divisions. Groups with the largest amount of material include the College of Arts and Sciences; College of Dentistry; Medical Center; Tisch School of the Arts; College and Graduate School of Business Administration; School of Education, Health, Nursing, and Arts Professions; Courant Institute of Mathematical Sciences; School of Law; School of Continuing Education; and Institute of Fine Arts. This series also contains files on NYU in Spain; the Gallatin Division; La Maison Française; Onassis Center for Hellenic Studies; and Deutsches Haus. Admissions reports on individual schools and the university date from 1977 to 1983. Meeting files for the Boards for the Medical Center, School of Arts and Science, and Law School Board are also in this series.

Series XII. Student Affairs, 1971-1991

Extent

6.70 Linear Feet in 16 manuscript boxes.

Scope and Contents

This series contains subjects relating to NYU students, including financial aid; housing; South African students at NYU; fraternities; sports teams; and student groups, such as the Gay Students Union. Files date from 1971 to 1991 and typically contain correspondence, reports, magazine articles, and press clippings. There are a significant number of files in this series containing admissions statistical reports and admission intervention request-related correspondence.

Arrangement

This series is arranged in chronological order.

Series XIII. Speeches and Writings, 1981-1991

Extent

22.50 Linear Feet in 54 manuscript boxes.
1 audiocassette
3 videocassettes (vhs)

Scope and Contents

This series contains John Bradmas' speeches, writings, and interviews while serving as President of NYU. The speeches (1981 to 1991) are from events including NYU graduations, Board of Trustee and Senate University meetings, and other public appearances. Speech files often contain final copy and drafts; notes; and informational memos containing event location, time/date, and background. Three of these speech files also include video recordings. Unless otherwise stated, the speeches were delivered by Brademas. Yearly NYU graduation ceremony files often contain detailed schedules, event programs, and speeches from all presenters. This series also contains op-ed pieces, articles, and memos written by Brademas. Presidential greetings and letters for use by various NYU publications are also in this series.

Series XIV. Correspondence, 1981-19901983-1986

Extent

3.30 Linear Feet in 8 manuscript boxes.

Scope and Contents

This series contains chronological correspondence files dating from 1981 to 1990, with the bulk from 1983 to 1986. Topics include communications with staff and faculty; discussions with politicians and heads of state; relations with potential and existing donors; and parents requesting intervention for admission.

Conditions Governing Access

Access to this series is restricted.
